  "prompt": "How do I get person online status when he is on whatsapp call?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, **WhatsApp does not publicly provide an official API or method to directly determine if a user is on a WhatsApp call**. This is due to privacy considerations and the end-to-end encryption that WhatsApp employs.\n\nHere's a breakdown of why you can't do it and what limitations you face:\n\n* **Privacy:** WhatsApp prioritizes user privacy.  Revealing call status would be a significant privacy breach, potentially exposing sensitive information about a user's activities.\n* **End-to-End Encryption:** WhatsApp's encryption prevents even WhatsApp themselves from knowing the content of calls or messages.  The information simply isn't available to be shared, even if they wanted to.\n* **Lack of Official API:**  WhatsApp's official API focuses on business-related interactions, not personal user status.  There are no functions to query whether a user is on a call.\n* **Third-Party Apps and Methods:** Any app claiming to do this is almost certainly:\n    * **Violating WhatsApp's Terms of Service:** This could lead to your WhatsApp account being banned.\n    * **Malware/Scam:**  These apps often steal your data or install malicious software.\n    * **Unreliable:** Even if they work temporarily, WhatsApp could easily block them with an update.\n\n**What you *might* observe (but not reliably):**\n\n* **Last Seen:** If a user has \"Last Seen\" enabled, it might not update while they are on a call. However, this isn't a guaranteed indicator.  They might have disabled \"Last Seen\" altogether, or it might update briefly after the call ends.\n* **Double Check Marks:** If you send a message, and it only shows one check mark (sent but not delivered to the recipient's phone) for an extended period, they *might* be on a call, but it could also mean:\n    * Their phone is off or has no internet connection.\n    * They have blocked you.\n    * They are in an area with poor connectivity.\n    * They have simply not opened WhatsApp.\n\n**In summary:** There is no reliable or ethical way to determine if someone is on a WhatsApp call.  Respect user privacy and avoid using any third-party apps that claim to do so.  They are likely to be scams or malware, and they violate WhatsApp's terms of service.\n",
